Key Match Events: Fernando Tatis Jr. has homered twice, improving to 9-for-14 to start his postseason.
Jackson Merrill and Xander Bogaerts connected on back-to-back home runs.
David Peralta hit a two-run homer against his former club.
Max Muncy hit a solo home run in the ninth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Max Muncy bluntly stated, 'We were s—.'
Dave Roberts commented on Freddie Freeman's uncertain status due to his ankle injury.
Mookie Betts reflected on his performance, saying, 'They’re all outs. So they’re all terrible.'
Miguel Rojas emphasized the need to improve hitting, defense, and pitching.
Dave Roberts mentioned the challenge of potentially playing without Freeman.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was marred by a seventh inning delay due to trash being thrown at Fernando Tatis Jr.
The Dodgers' pitching struggles were highlighted, with Jack Flaherty allowing four runs in 5 1/3 innings.
